{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd2739ee5-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5","identifier":"/us/usc/t47/s331"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"331"},"text":"§ 331.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Very high frequency stations and AM radio stations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd2739ee6-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5","identifier":"/us/usc/t47/s331/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Very high frequency stations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It shall be the policy of the Federal Communications Commission to allocate channels for very high frequency commercial television broadcasting in a manner which ensures that not less than one such channel shall be allocated to each State, if technically feasible. In any case in which licensee of a very high frequency commercial television broadcast station notifies the Commission to the effect that such licensee will agree to the reallocation of its channel to a community within a State in which there is allocated no very high frequency commercial television broadcast channel at the time ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002014"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002014"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be followed by “of”."}],"tail":" such notification, the Commission shall, notwithstanding any other provision of law, order such reallocation and issue a license to such licensee for that purpose pursuant to such notification for a term of not to exceed 5 years as provided in section 307(d) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002015"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002015"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd2739ee7-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5","identifier":"/us/usc/t47/s331/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" AM radio stations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It shall be the policy of the Commission, in any case in which the licensee of an existing AM daytime-only station located in a community with a population of more than 100,000 persons that lacks a local full-time aural station licensed to that community and that is located within a Class I station primary service area notifies the Commission that such licensee seeks to provide full-time service, to ensure that such a licensee is able to place a principal community contour signal over its entire community of license 24 hours a day, if technically feasible.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd2739ee8-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652"},"text":"June 19, 1934, ch. 652","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 331, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248/tIII/s355"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248, title III, § 355","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-03"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/641"},"text":"96 Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/243/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–243, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/2402"},"text":"105 Stat. 2402","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/414/tIII/s303/a/18"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–414, title III, § 303(a)(18)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-25"},"text":"Oct. 25, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4295"},"text":"108 Stat. 4295","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141/dP/tIV/s402/i/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141, div. P, title IV, § 402(i)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1089"},"text":"132 Stat. 1089","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd2739ee9-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd2739eea-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idd2739eeb-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t47/s307"},"text":"section 307 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (a), was redesignated subsec. (c) of section 307 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/259/tI/s112/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–259, title I, § 112(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1093"},"text":"96 Stat. 1093","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idd2739eec-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Another section 331 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-06-19"},"text":"June 19, 1934","children":[],"tail":" was renumbered section 332 and is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t47/s332"},"text":"section 332 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idd2739eed-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 331, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652/tIII/s331"},"text":"act June 19, 1934, ch. 652, title III, § 331","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-09-14"},"text":"Sept. 14, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/107/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–107, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/350"},"text":"87 Stat. 350","children":[],"tail":", related to broadcasting of games of professional sports clubs, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/107/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–107, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-09-14"},"text":"Sept. 14, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/351"},"text":"87 Stat. 351","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1975","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd2739eee-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141","children":[],"tail":" struck out at end: “The Commission shall report to the appropriate committees of Congress within 30 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-20"},"text":"December 20, 1991","children":[],"tail":", on how it intends to meet this policy goal.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/414"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–414","children":[],"tail":" amended section catchline generally."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/243"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–243","children":[],"tail":" inserted “and AM radio stations” in section catchline, designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and inserted heading, and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
